      "side": 1,
      "message": "It\u0027s a riddle, isn\u0027t it? I believe the answer lies in ArrayIndexTypes.glsl, which compiles down to:\n\n    sk_FragColor \u003d vec4(float[4](1.0, 2.0, 3.0, 4.0)[0], float[4](1.0, 2.0, 3.0, 4.0)[1u], float[4](1.0, 2.0, 3.0, 4.0)[2], float[4](1.0, 2.0, 3.0, 4.0)[3u]);\n\nThe array has been used, and fully constant-propagated, four times. We don\u0027t have a separate optimization for extracting a constant index from a constant array, though.\n\nI can imagine cases where this constant propagation might backfire spectacularly on us (large arrays?)",
